CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 01 Aug 2023 17:08:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690909709</ingested><modified> 2023-08-01T17:08:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="1439" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/9d89d4e0-308a-11ee-bdfa-cb75c0348a33" width="2549"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1439" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/9d89d4e0-308a-11ee-bdfa-cb75c0348a33" width="2549"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[20th Century Studios/Behaviour Interactive]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Xenomorph from Alien.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The Xenomorph from Alien]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best smart light bulbs for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>构建智能家居生态系统的最佳起点之一是智能灯泡。与其他物联网设备相比，它们不仅价格相对较低（每个灯泡的价格通常在 10 至 50 美元之间），而且还可以彻底改变您家的感觉。您可以在几分钟内从无聊和模拟变为丰富多彩和自动化，并且在使用智能灯泡创建时髦彩色灯光场景、设置时间表等方面有无限的可能性。</p><p>但与过去几年智能家居领域的其他领域一样，现在智能照明领域的参与者比以往任何时候都多。我们测试了市场上一些最受欢迎的智能灯，发现它们中的大多数都相当不错，但在兼容性、色彩质量和移动应用程序可用性方面存在差异，在决定哪种智能灯泡系统最好之前值得考虑为你的家购买。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2>购买智能灯泡需要注意什么</h2><h3>连接性（到集线器或不到集线器）</h3><p>智能灯最大的吸引力之一是能够通过手机控制它们。他们中的大多数人都可以通过 WiFi 或蓝牙或通过外部集线器连接来实现此目的，该集线器为他们处理连接。蓝牙连接限制了您控制灯光的范围，因此它只适合有限数量的灯泡以及您不希望在您离开时控制的灯泡。</p><p> WiFi 智能灯易于设置，而且总体上更便宜，因为它们不需要集线器来连接。然而，拥有中央 Zigbee 集线器之类的东西可以使您的整个系统更加可靠，因为它的连接与您家的 WiFi 网络是分开的。因此，基于集线器的灯泡往往更具可扩展性，因此如果您希望最终在家里拥有数十个智能灯，我们主要推荐这些灯泡。</p><h3>白色还是彩色？</h3><p>如今，您会发现的大多数智能灯泡都是“白色和彩色”灯泡，这意味着它们可以发出充满活力的蓝色、粉色、绿色以及介于两者之间的所有颜色，并发出不同温度的白色光。但也有一些纯白色灯泡，而且它们通常比彩色灯泡更便宜。虽然我们建议使用白色和彩色设备，但如果您只喜欢白色，请确保您购买的灯泡可以跨越色温光谱（通常从大约 2000 到 5000 开尔文），为您提供各种级别暖白光和冷白光。</p><h3>应用程序功能</h3><p>智能灯的好处之一是，由于其各种应用程序连接功能，您可以对它们进行控制。大多数配套应用程序都可以让您执行诸如设置照明时间表、将各个灯光分组到房间名称以及使用不同颜色创建您自己的自定义灯光“场景”等操作。但我们还看到了其他功能，这些功能并不像假期模式那样普遍，可以自动打开和关闭灯以增强家庭安全性，并与媒体同步，根据您正在听的音乐或播放的音乐来改变灯光的颜色。您当前正在直播的游戏。</p><h3>智能家居兼容性</h3><p>如果您经常使用亚马逊 Alexa 或 Google Assistant 等智能助手，请确保您获得的智能灯与您最喜欢的设备配合使用。我们测试的所有灯泡都支持亚马逊和谷歌的虚拟助手，允许您使用语音命令来打开和关闭灯、调暗灯光等等。这里的通配符是 Siri 和苹果的 HomeKit；虽然许多智能灯泡已将 HomeKit 添加到其兼容连接列表中，但并非所有灯都支持 Apple 的智能家居系统。</p><h3>扩展性</h3><p>我们在上面提到过这一点，但您需要考虑您的家中最终需要多少个智能灯。某些品牌和照明系统比其他品牌和照明系统更容易扩展，如果您打算在家中的每个房间都安装智能灯，我们通常建议您使用基于集线器的灯泡。如果您只想用一些精美的灯光来装饰您的家庭办公室或客厅，那么 WiFi 选项应该可以很好地满足您的需求。值得庆幸的是，这些是您可以获得的一些最实惠的智能家居设备，因此，即使您现在对这个问题没有明确的答案，如果您决定为您的家配备多个设备，您也可以重新考虑您的选择。智能灯泡。</p><h2>整体最佳：飞利浦 Hue White + Color Ambiance </h2><p><core-commerce id="e665469b83be43b7b36503e801838eb9" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您对智能灯进行过研究，您可能遇到过<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQKLiQdjMORv95p41OUxPUt4jIe2cH5EvxXjRYP4fZ7j&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPhilips-Hue-Bluetooth-compatible-Assistant%2Fdp%2FB07QV9XB87">飞利浦 Hue 灯泡</a>。该系列因多种原因而广受欢迎，我们一致认为，由于其广泛的兼容性、易于使用的移动应用程序和可扩展性，它们是您可以获得的最佳智能灯泡。特别是，如果您知道想要为家里的多个房间配备这些物联网设备，那么飞利浦 Hue 就是您的最佳选择。</p><p>关于 Hue 灯泡，首先要了解的是它们现在支持蓝牙。这意味着您可以先购买一些来试用，然后当您想为家里添加更多灯时，可以使用集线器轻松扩展您的系统。以前，任何和所有灯都需要集线器，但现在在完全投入之前先涉足该范围要容易得多。</p><p>与我们测试的所有其他智能灯一样，您只需拧入飞利浦 Hue 灯泡，打开灯，然后按照移动应用程序中的说明开始使用它。即使您只有一个房间内的灯光可供启动，我们仍然建议您在 Hue 应用程序中将它们分组到各自的“房间”中，以便您可以轻松地同时控制整个空间的环境。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQKLiQdjMORv95p41OUxPUt4jIe2cH5EvxXjRYP4fZ7j&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPhilips-Hue-Bluetooth-compatible-Assistant%2Fdp%2FB07QV9XB87">Hue 的白色 + 彩色</a>灯泡提供一系列暖白色到冷白色以及数百万种颜色，供您在智能家居中进行实验。颜色丰富且充满活力，飞利浦的预编程场景（例如“活力”、“明亮”和“放松”）可让您快速模仿旧的“哑光”灯光以及不同温暖级别的白光。您也可以从应用程序中的多种颜色场景中进行选择，但创建自己的色温也很容易。因此，如果您一直希望在 Twitch 上进行直播时让您的办公室充满彩虹般的鲜艳色彩，您可以找到您想要的精确预设，保存它们，然后只需在应用程序。</p><p> Hue 应用程序非常易于使用，灯泡支持来自亚马逊 Alexa 和 Google Assistant 的语音命令。这意味着您甚至不必打开应用程序来控制灯光；您只需使用语音控制并说“Alexa，关闭卧室的灯”，只有指定房间的灯才会熄灭。仅使用蓝牙，您就可以向系统添加最多 10 个灯泡，此时您必须添加飞利浦 Hue 集线器以支持最多 50 个灯泡。该中心还支持 HomeKit 连接、灯光时间表和自动化、家庭和离开模式以及与电影和音乐同步等功能。</p><p>可以说，这些功能中最有用的是自动化，它可以让您设置灯的开/关时间表，包括当您离开家时自动关灯。这是可以理解的，为什么飞利浦会将这几个功能专门用于具有 Hue 集线器的设备 - 在组合中添加集线器可以使系统更加可靠，让您可以通过增加连接的灯数量来完成更多任务，此外，它还会鼓励许多人投资集线器随着时间的推移，会有更多的 Hue 灯泡。我们喜欢 Hue 的集线器，不仅因为它的可靠性，还因为它允许对您的设备进行更精细、更灵活的控制。因此，如果您在度假并想打开客厅的灯看看发生了什么，您可以这样做。</p><p>可扩展性超出了智能家居中灯的数量：它还包括多个您也可以安装在室外的智能灯泡。 Hue 系列有大量室内和室外灯泡可供选择，包括嵌入式灯、室外基座和泛光灯、灯带等。它是当今为数不多的几个系列之一，为您提供了大量的选择，使您家中进出的每个灯泡都变得智能，如果您知道自己想全力投入智能灯领域，那么考虑这一点很重要。</p><p>但这给我们带来了飞利浦 Hue 最大的缺点，那就是价格。 Hue 灯泡价格昂贵，两包白色 + 彩色氛围灯泡售价 80 美元。如果您正在寻找便宜的灯泡来测试智能照明，下面我们的其他一些首选产品（例如 Kasa 智能灯泡）将是更好的选择，因为它们中的大多数每个灯泡的价格较低。然而，如果您想在未来投资智能照明，我们建议您使用飞利浦的 Hue 入门套件之一： <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9QaGlsaXBzLUh1ZS1TdGFydGVyLUNvbXBhdGlibGUtQXNzaXN0YW50L2RwL0IwOTVLUVNYWUg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZ3MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMxN2RkNDJhLTI3YzktNGViYy1iZGMwLTlhNDNjNmQyNGMwOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQL-pui21HZF1vUC5rEEgjkEBsX6zl4Zo8WKfF5yhXES&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPhilips-Hue-Starter-Compatible-Assistant%2Fdp%2FB095KQSXYH">白色 + 彩色 Ambiance 入门套件</a>，包括三个灯泡、一个集线器和一个智能按钮，售价 180 美元，这比单独购买所有这些组件要便宜。</p><h2>亚军：LIFX Color A19 </h2><p><core-commerce id="a07c0747ccbb4b2094f9654dbff5fa13" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>总体而言，LIFX 的彩色智能灯与 Hue 的 White + Ambiance 灯泡相似，因为它们易于设置，提供引人注目的饱和色彩，并可与三大平台配合使用：Alexa、Google Assistant 和 HomeKit。但主要区别是 LIFX 灯泡仅支持 WiFi，因此即使您愿意，也无法将它们连接到集线器，而且有些灯泡比 Hue 设备稍贵一些。 The <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUpzdy1WeA4afh2sFMK2BEeiGJRFluHCqPpYdT8uX1Wk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLIFX-Color-1100lm-Edison-Screw%2Fdp%2FB08BKXPX3N">Color A19 bulb</a> , which supports 1100 lumens, normally costs $50, but there&#39;s an <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb-D7JUnuh6yQsZTmArpSNcRrz0jxJahwWcSXlTSY6s_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLIFX-Color-800lm-Edison-Screw%2Fdp%2FB08BL16M81%3F">800-lumen equivalent</a> that&#39;s a bit cheaper, coming in at $35 per bulb.</p><p> LIFX&#39;s mobile app is also undoubtedly the slickest we tested. While that may not mean much to you, it&#39;s worth mentioning because mobile apps are the way most people interact with their smart lights on a daily basis. The homepage features all of the room groups in your household, along with the names of the lights in each room. You can easily turn a whole room, or a specific light, on with just a tap, and do the same for all of the lights in your smart home.</p><p> LIFX lights support scheduling, so you can program lights to work for you so you rarely (if ever) have to control them manually, plus there are a plethora of scenes and effects to choose from. While all of the color lights we tried had pre-made scenes or presets ready to go in the app, Philips Hue and LIFX clearly had the most out of them all. Personally, I found LIFX&#39;s scenes and additional effects to be a bit more fun and engaging than Hue&#39;s. You can pick from scenes like “spooky” or “pastel” and use effects like “strobe” if you want to make your living room feel a bit more like a nightclub. While most people probably won&#39;t use these niche scenes and effects on a regular basis, they&#39;re great perks to have when you&#39;re entertaining or just want to set the right vibe for your next movie night or game-streaming session.</p><p> LIFX has a <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYADPCWjJK-X-559-kI6ulGQTqZzglIKB8lkURHJg2M-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2Fnode%2F9029830011%3Fie%3DUTF8%26field-lbr_brands_browse-bin%3DLIFX">number of products</a> in its ecosystem, from standard A19 bulbs to lightstrips to candles. It has switches, too, so you can physically control your smart lights if you wish. But Philips Hue has all of those options too and more, including not just switches, but standalone floor lamps, outdoor spotlights, downlights, light bars and motion sensors. You&#39;ll have more options with Hue if you want to convert all of your home&#39;s lights to smart ones, and have multiple ways to control them, too.</p><h2> Best budget: TP-Link Kasa Smart WiFi Light Bulb </h2><p><core-commerce id="28d08bd389cd4a30a06f27bc4c4407b3" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> TP-Link&#39;s Kasa brand is known for its solid yet affordable smart home devices and its smart lights are no different. We tested out the <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUs4nz_l_NZXPfTFwuGgGq-hzPaiJLEsPQWCXOZyBmq9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FKasa-Smart-Changing-Dimmable-Compatible%2Fdp%2FB08TB8Z5HF">WiFi-only multicolor smart light bulbs</a> and found them easy to install and use, and they provide a bunch of features at an affordable price; a four-pack of multicolor bulbs will only set you back $40.</p><p> Besides having a simple installation process, Kasa&#39;s multicolor smart lights stayed reliably connected the whole time we tested them and the companion mobile app is simple and clean. All of the main functions for each light live in that bulb&#39;s dedicated page in the app, allowing you to change brightness, white levels, color, schedules and more without navigating through a bunch of different menus. Changing colors is nearly instantaneous, and the light changes as you drag your finger across the color wheel in the app. Editing the four presets you&#39;re able to save takes only a few taps, as does grouping multiple bulbs into rooms and creating lighting schedules. For the latter, if you do set on/off schedules, the app will show you the next step in that schedule (ie, off at 8:35pm) next to each individual light.</p><p> There&#39;s also a handy “usage” section in each light&#39;s page that shows you the bulb&#39;s energy use over time, plus an estimate of how much energy you&#39;re saving by using a smart light instead of a regular one. This is something that would be fun to observe over many weeks and months of using these bulbs, especially if conserving energy is one of the main reasons you invested in smart lights in the first place.</p><p> TP-Link claims you can connect “unlimited” smart devices to its mobile app, which technically means you can have as many Kasa smart lights in your home as you&#39;d like. We only tested a few together, so we can&#39;t say for sure how dozens of connected devices would affect app speed and light response time. These are WiFi-only bulbs, which means connecting them to a Zigbee hub isn&#39;t an option, so keep that in mind before deciding to invest in a house-full of these gadgets. It&#39;s also worth noting that these lights aren&#39;t compatible with Apple&#39;s HomeKit, although you can control them using Alexa and Google Assistant commands.</p><h2> Best all white: LIFX White E26 </h2><p><core-commerce id="fe0539056c8a4ed78f5993f35e4ff6ce" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Maybe you don&#39;t want to bother with colored lights. If that&#39;s the case, <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwODY1VFJENUw_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZ3MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMxN2RkNDJhLTI3YzktNGViYy1iZGMwLTlhNDNjNmQyNGMwOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASTMwC65XBa7Qey988tEYbgemsv7y1T9uqIA_rsoF_fZ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0865TRD5L">LIFX&#39;s White E26</a> is your best bet. You get all of the non-color features in the mobile app that we explained above, including schedules and virtual assistant controls, but in a more basic LED light bulb that only costs $10.</p><p> My biggest gripe is that it doesn&#39;t span the cool-to-warm temperature range that other white bulbs do. Rather, you&#39;re stuck with just one shade of white: 2700K, which is on the warmer side. This makes the LIFX bulb better for intimate settings like a bedroom or a living room, but since it&#39;s not overly warm, it could work in a home office, too. It&#39;s also dimmable, so you can control its brightness.</p><p> If you have a specific use case in mind for your smart lights that doesn&#39;t involve a rainbow of colors, then a LIFX bulb will more than suffice. They would work well in a child&#39;s room, for instance, allowing you to set wake-up and sleep schedules that gradually turn on and off the lights, or in a home office where you just want a bit more control over your lights without extra frills.</p><h2> Honorable mention: Sengled Smart Light Bulbs </h2><p><core-commerce id="92f4d2dcc31744cbaf23ec6326c0038d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1;pdid:Sengled’s Smart Light Bulbs" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TZW5nbGVkLUNoYW5naW5nLUFzc2lzdGFudC1SZXF1aXJlZC1FcXVpdmFsZW50L2RwL0IwOTFGUVJCVEw_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZ3MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMxN2RkNDJhLTI3YzktNGViYy1iZGMwLTlhNDNjNmQyNGMwOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAW-a8TYKAV1J3qL9HPNPmEIUF5E60u00YSgxGK6nrQv_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSengled-Changing-Assistant-Required-Equivalent%2Fdp%2FB091FQRBTL" data-demonetize-referrer="https://amzn.to/37LnR3d" class="rapid-with-clickid">Sengled&#39;s Smart Light Bulbs</a> deserve a shout because they&#39;re essentially more affordable versions of the best bulbs mentioned here, just with a few compromises. Key among those is that their colors are less nuanced than most others we tested and the mobile app is less polished.</p><p> That said, you&#39;re still getting millions of colors out of Sengled&#39;s smart lights and the app is easy to use. It also provides all of the features you&#39;d want from a smart light bulb, including grouping, schedules and automations. The fact that the Sengled mobile app isn&#39;t as slick as Hue&#39;s or LIFX&#39;s may actually work in its favor with newbies – the basic controls and labels will be very easy for smart home novices to understand.</p><p> The bulbs we tested were WiFi-based, so they do not require a hub. However, Sengled has a bunch of other smart lights that work via WiFi, Bluetooth or hub connectivity. A pack of four <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1;pdid:WiFi color bulbs" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TZW5nbGVkLUNoYW5naW5nLUFzc2lzdGFudC1SZXF1aXJlZC1FcXVpdmFsZW50L2RwL0IwOTFGUVJCVEw_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZ3MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMxN2RkNDJhLTI3YzktNGViYy1iZGMwLTlhNDNjNmQyNGMwOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAW-a8TYKAV1J3qL9HPNPmEIUF5E60u00YSgxGK6nrQv_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSengled-Changing-Assistant-Required-Equivalent%2Fdp%2FB091FQRBTL" data-demonetize-referrer="https://amzn.to/37LnR3d" class="rapid-with-clickid">WiFi color bulbs</a> will set you back $30, while a set of <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1;pdid:six Zigbee hub-based lights" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdoeCmQ5QEl40JG3nkMFdnymbiVpxKVBWD1biLSacgW9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSengled-Required-SmartThings-Control-Changing%2Fdp%2FB092D72L6M" data-demonetize-referrer="https://amzn.to/3JDYYU4" class="rapid-with-clickid">six Zigbee hub-based lights</a> costs only $100. Overall, Sengled&#39;s devices are much more affordable than Hue&#39;s, making them a good budget option regardless of whether you want to stick to WiFi or invest in a smart home hub like <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:12;pos:1;pdid:Sengled’s own" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TZW5nbGVkLVowMi1odWItU21hcnQtSHViLVdoaXRlL2RwL0IwN0hLU1RMQjU_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZ3MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMxN2RkNDJhLTI3YzktNGViYy1iZGMwLTlhNDNjNmQyNGMwOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAARPx-QCXthkFCmI9KjzGVYllnkdX5-1GSAPxsQ3w6Aj7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSengled-Z02-hub-Smart-Hub-White%2Fdp%2FB07HKSTLB5" data-demonetize-referrer="https://amzn.to/3rjULPa" class="rapid-with-clickid">Sengled&#39;s own</a> or a smart device like <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:13;pos:1;pdid:Amazon’s Echo" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATddu0X7r1SBWm-OhUw_CULcGX7dsnBBAlnRmK5jNvjL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAll-New-Echo-4th-Gen%2Fdp%2FB07XKF5RM3" data-demonetize-referrer="https://amzn.to/3E7ZnNw" class="rapid-with-clickid">Amazon&#39;s Echo</a> with a built-in hub.</p><h2> Best smart lamp: Philips Hue Signe Table Lamp </h2><p><core-commerce id="a94984eed06b413e85b92f51960923ec" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATR8PCTSgEP5CgXeRCYdH4ny9h9aQKuhjp3rjI9SoVXj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPhilips-Hue-573733-Gradient-Signe%2Fdp%2FB09BDKV84P">Philips&#39; Signe table lamp</a> is a slick way to add a wash of color into your living room, or a more controllable light source on your desk. The nearly two-foot tall lamp can be customized with up to three colors of light at once, plus it supports a full array of cool and warm hues as well. Shine it towards a wall to set the mood with colored lights during your game night, or use it to give yourself sufficient lighting during your next Zoom meeting – you can make it as fun or as practical as you need. It also supports effects like “candle” and “fireplace,” both of which produce moving light that emulates flickering flames. We also appreciate that the Signe lamp is a totally standalone device, like most of Philips&#39; new Hue bulbs: you don&#39;t need a Hue bridge to use it. But if you have one, you&#39;ll be able to do things like control the lamp when you&#39;re away from home.</p><p> The Signe lamp is a splurge, though, coming in at over $200. It&#39;s certainly worth it if you need just one powerful light source, but a more affordable alternative would be the <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfzYxyNRNEzxUYuRrTwQak0NkhzTtFMxSmw-W4AXwppl&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPhilips-Hue-Portable-Dimmable-Assistant%2Fdp%2FB00UVHAC1O">Philips Hue Go portable table lamp</a> . It too supports millions of colors and a full spectrum of warm and cool light, but it runs on a rechargeable battery and can be used wirelessly. Depending on the setting you choose, you&#39;ll get up to 18 hours of continuous use, making it a good option if you want a controllable light that can go anywhere you need it without fuss.</p><h2> Best smart light strip: Govee M1 RGBIC LED Strip Light </h2><p><core-commerce id="7f9b12877f2f4910947ee6b4e4a05a2c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Light strips can bring illumination to hard-to-reach places, or give a whole new vibe to your living room or office. The latest light strip from Govee, the <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfGgpxxsLTsxRxLGF9ATujGF3SNoCaPzAfu308bin0C1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGovee-Upgraded-Technology-Compatible-Christmas%2Fdp%2FB0B42BWVLM%2F">M1 RGBIC model</a> , gets super bright and supports a wide range of colors. It&#39;s WiFi-connected but requires no central hub, so even if you have other smart lights throughout your home, this one will fit in easily. One strip measures nearly 16.5 feet long and it&#39;s divided into 15 segments that you can control individually from within the Govee app.</p><p> We&#39;ll get into the app features, but it&#39;s worth noting where the M1 sits in the smart light strip space. There are various different lengths out there and you can even find some two-packs that will cover <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAS6nqE35DB4ZMEpBi5AZoQO6bfwbnes2MbktcOZOaWtn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDAYBETTER-Control-Bedroom-Decoration-Assistant%2Fdp%2FB09982KTLY%2F">up to 100 feet</a> . The 16.4-foot length is pretty common in single packs, although you can find some that run <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYP-Vg0iu988PGJl3uoHkExYlTL3FMPx2ygtHmhbCofw&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGovee-Control-Segmented-Bluetooth-Changing%2Fdp%2FB099S9DXT7">up to 33 feet long</a> . You can expect to pay $25 to $50 for a basic, multi-color, 16.4-foot light strip and the price will go up from there depending on how many segments the strip has, the color range it supports, if it&#39;s WiFi-connected and other additional features. Govee&#39;s M1 Light Strip is on the higher end of the spectrum, coming in at $110 for 16.4 feet of light, but it still costs less than arguably its biggest competitor: Philips&#39; Hue Light Strips, which come in at <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9QaGlsaXBzLUh1ZS1CbHVldG9vdGgtTGlnaHRzdHJpcC1Db21wYXRpYmxlL2RwL0IwOENLSldTRlM_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZ3MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMxN2RkNDJhLTI3YzktNGViYy1iZGMwLTlhNDNjNmQyNGMwOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAVU4xTfnggJbb54IFCX6ZX3PoPetCquQIsVjGf5G4vFI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPhilips-Hue-Bluetooth-Lightstrip-Compatible%2Fdp%2FB08CKJWSFS">$80 per 6-foot strip</a> .</p><p> I was impressed by not only the color spectrum the M1 Light Strip supports, but also how bright it is. This strip gets almost blinding, and I usually had it operating at just 75 percent of its full brightness. While you can&#39;t control each individual light on the strip, you can customize all 15 segments in the Govee app.</p><p> The sheer number of options and effects Govee provides is remarkable: the “effects lab” gives you pre-made basic colors, scenes that mimic sunrises, starry nights, different kinds of movies like thrillers and dramas, gaming genres and more. On top of that, you can make your own custom scenes (and choose to share them with others in Govee&#39;s Explore page) as well as your favorite colors and hues that you can save for frequent use. The strip&#39;s color is saturated and vibrant – combine that with the overall brightness and it was easily able to give my office an attractive, ambient glow when positioned around the periphery of my couch.</p><p> Aside from the higher price tag, my only other complaint about the M1 light strip is actually Govee&#39;s mobile app. It&#39;s a bit chaotic and takes some getting used to, so it might not be the best choice for anyone that wants something basic. However, I was able to get the hang of all the controls, and then some, after about a half hour. And you can always default to using Alexa or Google Assistant voice commands to control your light strip if you prefer, or you can set automations in the app that can take care of all your most used controls.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-led-light-bulbs-143022856.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-led-light-bulbs-143022856.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c17dd42a-27c9-4ebc-bdc0-9a43c6d24c08<